    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>cauliflower</strong> into large florets, discard the stem and leaves</p><p>Add the <strong>cauliflower florets</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until beginning to crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!) and combine with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate pot over a medium heat with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>peanut butter</strong>,<strong> gluten free soy sauce </strong>and <strong>coconut stock </strong>to the pot with 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 6-8 min or until the sauce thickens, stirring occasionally</p><p>Once thickened, remove the pot from the heat, add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, then stir it all together and set aside to cool \u2013 this is your <strong>peanut dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Roughly chop your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, fluff the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a fork and add to a large bowl with your <strong>carrot & cabbage slaw mix </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped herbs </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)</p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>peanut dressing </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the bowl and toss \u2013 this is your<strong> rainbow salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/roasted-cauliflower-rainbow-salad-with-peanut-dressing/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>rainbow salad</strong> and top with the <strong>roasted cauliflower florets</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining peanut dressing </strong>and garnish with the <strong>remaining chopped herbs</strong>, <strong>chopped peanuts</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
